column2: # = High output engine that provides more power than the standard engine of the same size
Fuel consumption ratings are shown in litres per 100 kilometres (L/100 km) and in miles per imperial gallon (mpg)
Estimated annual fuel use is based on 20 000 km driven and a combined rating of 55 percent city and 45 percent highway.
Estimated tailpipe carbon dioxide emissions (in grams per kilometre) are based on fuel type and the combined fuel consumption rating.
